Cilla (BBC TV series)
Cilla (BBC TV series)
Black was offered her own show on the BBC by Bill Cotton, then Assistant Head of Light Entertainment.

Cotton considered Black to take over from Bruce Forsyth as host of The Generation Game in 1978, but after a brief conversation, Cotton learned that Black wanted to maintain her singing career and was not ready to change course so drastically to light entertainment hostess.
